---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import RouteConsole from "../components/RouteConsole.astro";
const selectedPackageReleaseTag = "v0.2.1";
---

<SiteLayout title="ShardLoom" description="Evidence-gated compute over Vortex-native routes, explicit outputs, and claim-safe benchmark proof." path="/" active="home">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Technical preview</p>
      <h1>ShardLoom</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        A standalone encoded-columnar engine for Vortex-native routes, explicit output plans, and benchmark evidence that says what was timed.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="/start">Start local proof</a>
        <a class="button" href="/field-guide">Read Field Guide</a>
        <a class="button ghost" href="/benchmarks">Open benchmark comparison</a>
      </div>
      <div class="status-chips" aria-label="Current posture">
        <span>technical preview</span><span>no fallback</span><span>Vortex-first</span><span>claim-gated</span><span>package track selected</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <RouteConsole />
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="strip">
      <div class="metric"><strong>Vortex</strong><span>native route target</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong>false</strong><span>fallback execution</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong>ClickBench</strong><span>public comparison target</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong>{selectedPackageReleaseTag}</strong><span>latest public package train</span></div>
      <div class="metric"><strong>false</strong><span>fallback/external engine for ShardLoom rows</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Benchmark posture</p>
      <h2>Public comparisons belong on ClickBench.</h2>
      <p class="narrow">ShardLoom keeps local benchmark artifacts for engineering validation, but shardloom.io no longer renders them as a public leaderboard. The public comparison path points to ClickBench while ShardLoom-specific route evidence stays in the Field Guide.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card"><span class="badge">ClickBench</span><h3>External leaderboard.</h3><p>The website links to the upstream ClickBench comparison surface rather than mirroring local artifact rankings.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span class="badge">Evidence</span><h3>Route proof remains local.</h3><p>ShardLoom route diagnostics still expose timing surface, evidence tier, and claim gates in CLI/Python outputs.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span class="badge">Boundary</span><h3>No hidden execution fallback.</h3><p>External engines stay baselines and correctness references, never execution substitutes for ShardLoom routes.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span class="badge">Release</span><h3>Claims require named proof.</h3><p>Any published result should state route, format, dataset, source version, and whether load time is included.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Route contract</p>
      <h2>Compute routes should be inspectable.</h2>
      <p class="narrow">ShardLoom keeps source admission, Vortex preparation, execution, output, and evidence separate so unsupported work blocks deterministically.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card"><span class="badge">Evidence</span><h3>Rows carry proof fields.</h3><p>ShardLoom emits <code>fallback_attempted</code>, <code>external_engine_invoked</code>, timing surface, evidence tier, and claim gate fields.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span class="badge">Timing</span><h3>Route totals name their surface.</h3><p>Certified cold, prepare-once, warm prepared, native Vortex, baseline, and publication proof are labeled separately.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span class="badge">Output</span><h3>Sinks are explicit route work.</h3><p>OutputPlan and SinkArtifact keep native output, compatibility fanout, replay, and evidence render separate from hot runtime.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><span class="badge">No fallback</span><h3>Unsupported paths fail closed.</h3><p>External engines are baselines only, never fallback execution for ShardLoom rows.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Try it</p>
      <h2>Start with the package surface.</h2>
      <p class="narrow">The public site shows runnable local posture and the selected local/source/package v1 release track without implying production support or broad SQL/DataFrame readiness. GitHub pre-release assets, TestPyPI, PyPI, and Homebrew are the current {selectedPackageReleaseTag} package channels with proof refs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="code-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Python surface shape</div>
      <pre><code>import shardloom as sl

ctx = sl.context()
result = (
    ctx.read("orders.csv")
       .filter(sl.col("status") == "paid")
       .limit(10)
       .collect()
)

print(result.evidence["claim_gate_status"])</code></pre>
      <div class="code-evidence"><span><strong>fallback_attempted</strong>false</span><span><strong>external_engine_invoked</strong>false</span><span><strong>claim_gate_status</strong>visible</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
